 succeeded in 0ms:
   129	### §A.1 Artifact trust boundary
   130	
   131	The chunk-9c helper
   132	`routes/_helpers.read_proposal_rationale(proposal, artifacts_dir)`
   133	takes a `Proposal` argument; chunk 9d wants the **same security
   134	envelope** (file://, contained in `--artifacts-dir`, ≤ 1 MiB) for
   135	**two URI-backed sources**: the proposal's rationale (via
   136	`proposal.artifacts_uri`) and the trial's `artifacts_uri` (when
   137	set by the implementer per §3.2 step 3). The trial's
   138	`description` is **not** URI-backed — it's free-form text stored
   139	directly on the trial — and is rendered through Jinja2's default
   140	autoescape; it does not go through this helper.
   141	
   142	The cleanest path is to generalize the existing helper:
   143	
   144	- Add a new internal helper
   145	  `_read_inline_artifact(uri: str | None, artifacts_dir: Path) -> str | None`
   146	  that takes a raw URI string and applies the same trust-boundary
   147	  rules.
   148	- Reimplement `read_proposal_rationale(proposal, artifacts_dir)`
   149	  as a thin wrapper that calls
   150	  `_read_inline_artifact(proposal.artifacts_uri, artifacts_dir)`,
   151	  preserving the existing call site signature so the chunk-9c
   152	  implementer module's import does not break.
   153	- The evaluator route uses `_read_inline_artifact` directly for
   154	  `trial.artifacts_uri` (and re-uses `read_proposal_rationale`
   155	  for the proposal rationale).
   156	
   157	Result: one trust-boundary implementation, two call sites in
   158	chunk 9d, identical envelope. The Phase 0 "no new helper"
   159	language was incorrect; chunk 9d ships the
   160	`_read_inline_artifact` extraction. Tests in
   161	`test_evaluator_security.py` (§I.4) cover trial-side `file://`
   162	confinement, traversal escape, non-`file://` schemes, the > 1 MiB
   163	cap, and directory inputs explicitly — we don't trust the
   164	symmetric proposal-side coverage from chunk 9c to flow through.
   165	
   166	The **trial's own** `artifacts_uri` and `description` MAY be set by
   167	the implementer on a successful `starting` trial (per
   168	`spec/v0/03-roles.md` §3.2 step 3). The chunk-9c implementer module
   169	already wires `description` into `Trial(...)` from its form input;
   170	`trial.artifacts_uri` is reserved for a future implementer-side
   171	artifact-upload feature. The evaluator's draft page therefore
   172	renders both `trial.description` (when set, as a read-only block,
   173	escaped via Jinja2 autoescape) and `trial.artifacts_uri` (when
   174	set, with the chunk-9c scheme allowlist applied: only `http`,
   175	`https`, and `file` schemes are hyperlinked; any other scheme
   176	renders as `<code>` plus "(unrenderable scheme)"). When
   177	`trial.artifacts_uri` is a `file://` URI inside `--artifacts-dir`
   178	and ≤ 1 MiB, the helper inlines the content — same envelope as
   179	the proposal rationale.
   180	

 succeeded in 0ms:
   425	The single-step structure means there's no Phase-1-failed /
   426	Phase-2-failed split. The submit either succeeds, definitively
   427	fails (rendered as a form error or orphan), or transport-fails
   428	into the read-back arm.
   429	
   430	### §C-recovery (per-error)
   431	
   432	| Outcome | Definition | UI rendering | Operator action |
   433	|---|---|---|---|
   434	| ok | submit returned cleanly OR retry returned cleanly OR read-back found equivalent prior submission | `evaluator_submitted.html`, 200 | none |
   435	| InvalidPrecondition (form-time, e.g. metric type drift only the server caught) | server rejected the metrics shape | re-render draft with the wire-error banner attached | fix the metrics and resubmit |
   436	| WrongToken | the prior reclaim invalidated our claim (sweeper or operator) | orphan, `recovery_kind="auto"` | none — prior reclaim already restored task to `pending` |
   437	| IllegalTransition, read-back finds state==pending | sweeper reclaimed our claim before our submit committed | orphan, `recovery_kind="auto"` | none |
   438	| IllegalTransition, read-back finds equivalent prior submission | our prior attempt committed; orchestrator already terminalized | success page (treated as `ok`) | none |
   439	| IllegalTransition, read-back finds non-equivalent submission | a different submission won the race; we lost | orphan, `recovery_kind="conflict"` | operator triage |
   440	| ConflictingResubmission | a different submission won the race for this task | orphan, `recovery_kind="conflict"` | operator triage; the system's record stands |
   441	| transport, retry exhausted, claim still ours | network glitch persisted; claim TTL will eventually reclaim | orphan, `recovery_kind="auto"` | wait for TTL, or operator-side reclaim |
   442	| transport, retry exhausted, server committed equivalent | "submitted, response lost" sub-case A | success page (treated as `ok`) | none |
   443	| transport, retry exhausted, server committed non-equivalent | "different submission won" sub-case A' | orphan, `recovery_kind="conflict"` | operator triage |
   444	| transport, retry exhausted, store invariant violated | implementation-illegal: terminal task with no recorded submission | orphan, `recovery_kind="transport"` | operator investigation |
   445	| transport, retry exhausted, read-back probe itself failed | indeterminate | orphan, `recovery_kind="transport"` | operator investigation |

